This board has helped me with a lot of useful information from the
beginning of my journey but the journey is about to end. I'm a USC, we
were married on 11/02 and got our conditional GC on 11/04, three days
before our 2nd wedding anniversary. Our marriage was great until my ex
started to appear into my life. we started having arguments constantly
ever since. To make the story short, I could not take it anymore so I
asked her for a divorce. She's doesn't want a divorce b/c of the
filing of the i-751 and the interview. I told her there's nothing to
worry about since she can file on her own and we have evidence of a bona
fide marriage. I am ready to move on without having these constant
headaches. Should I stay and filed i-751 with her for another year or
hell with it get a divorce and move on?

--
