This isn't my situation and I don't know you or your wife, so I can just
give you my uninformed opinion, but you asked for it so here you go! :)

You have a life to live, and apparently, it's not going to include your
current wife. You should file for your divorce and start moving on.
Putting your entire life on hold so that she can advance hers doesn't
make sense if it's just a matter of time before she's out the door. Why
is her life more important than yours? It seems she thinks you should
make sacrifices for her so that she won't have to make any sacrifices
herself. Seems very unfair to me!

As for her refusing or not wanting a divorce, well, this is America and
tough luck, but one partner wanting a divorce is enough.

So, go for it. You only have one life, and there is no sense in giving
up part of it for someone who won't give anything up for you.

