You don't have to go to the interview with her. I believe she becomes
deportable one year after the I-751 is filed unless she successfully has
the conditions removed.

I'd say that her wanting to pretend to be happily married for
immigration purposes shows how she feels about marriage, and is somewhat
dishonest.

As for the I-864, has anyone ever heard of one actually being enforced?

